0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume combines narratological analyses with an investigation of the ideological ramifications of the use of narrative strategies. The collected essays do not posit any intrinsic or stable connection between narrative techniques and world views. Rather, they demonstrate that world views are inevitably expressed through highly specific formal strategies. This insight leads the contributors to investigate why and how particular narrative techniques are employed and under what conditions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDiscourse analysis, Literary. 0aDiscourse analysis, Narrative. 0aNarration (Rhetoric) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aExperientiality.  acognitive narratology.  adiachronic perspective.  aideology.  anarrative features.1 aAlber, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlber, Jan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBirke, Dorothee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaracciolo, Marco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarrard, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChrist, Birte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aContzen, Eva von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuffield, Hilary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFest, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohlmann, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLanser, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Wolfgang